Amani National Congress party leader Musalia Mudavadi is expected to pitch tent in Mombasa on Saturday and Sunday to prepare ground for a NASA mega rally.The date for the rally will be communicated later. To weeks ago, Mudavadi toured Kilifi.ANC national chairman Kelvin Lunani yesterday said Mudavadi will go to Mombasa on Saturday and hold rallies in Changamwe, Jomvu and Mvita constituencies .&ldquo;There will be mini rallies at Akamba handicraft and Amani Primary School. At ACK Makupa, he will meet Mulembe nation as their spokesperson,&rdquo; he said on the phone.Lunani said Mudavadi will open the ANC regional office in Tudor, hold another rally at Maweni Secondary School then host the party's aspirants for a dinner.&ldquo;At Maweni I will make a major declaration to be ratified by Mudavadi,&rdquo; he said.On Sunday, the ANC boss will attend a church service at Shanzu Catholic Church and then head to Tudor at Friends Quakers Church to launch a bus.Mudavadi will then meet the Muslim community at the Swahili Cultural Centre.He will wind up his tour with a rally at Likoni Total ground.&ldquo;During various meetings, he will discuss the stake of Luhyas in Mombasa,&rdquo; Lunani said.The community has been negotiating for Nyali MP seat, speaker seat, three slots for nominated MCAs and four executive members.Lunani has been championing the cause. He said community will support the governor candidate who meets their demands.Beside ANC affairs, Mudavadi will also campaign for NASA and present it as the only option to dislodge Jubilee from power.Mombasa is considered an opposition stronghold.The NASA mega rally is expected to attended by the four leaders &mdash; Mudavadi, Raila Odinga (ODM), Kalonzo Musyoka (Wiper) and Moses Wetang'ula (Ford Kenya.The four have already toured Eldoret, Tharaka Nithi and Meru to hunt for votes. They headed to Wajir on yesterday.